description.value: During design and manufacture, a SW Developer introduces software to the Fire Control Application that redirects Operator fire commands, when deployed at a specific geographic location. With this Cyber-attack knowledge, a Physical attacker could gain access to a protected area.​
During operation of the Silverfish network, a Cyber Attacker gains access to the Radio Relay network and injects false IR sensor report messages.

During design and manufacture, a SW Developer introduces software to the IR Sensor that delays sensor reports when deployed at a specific geographic location. With this Cyber-attack knowledge, a Physical attacker could gain access to a protected area.

During deployment, malware is injected that prevents setting obstacle location.

Sentinel stores boot integrity totp for each obstacle in order to detect tampering of sw / os / application / configuration.
Sufficient delay to allow physical attacker to cross field.​
